         Another change they would have to make. if DoT's were coded as rain spells, is to allow the DoT's to travel with the mob.  I thought rain spells were location specific and were just centered on something, either the caster or a mob.</P><P>Frankly, I would prefer they give us another affliction line of focus items that increases our DoT damage by a flat 25% or 30%.  Then give us DoT criticals as a class AA ability for a flat 5/10/15 percent increase in DoT daamage.  And then give us a class Affliction Mastery skill for an additional 10% DoT damage.  That would put us more in line with what DD casters have.  The Extended Affliction and Affliction Efficiency items do not give us more DPS...just more efficient use of our mana.  We need more DPS.</P><P><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=157918" target=new>Ishtarra Gemeinseele </a><BR>Warlock of the Dirty Soul<BR>Uber N00b Extraordinaire<BR>Tunare Server<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
